      "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/34/1/20/5178",
      "text": [
        ": \"إِنَّمَا جُعِلَتِ اَلْقَسَامَةُ لِيُغَلَّظَ بِهَا فِي اَلرَّجُلِ اَلْمَعْرُوفِ بِالشَّرِّ اَلْمُتَّهَمِ فَإِنْ شَهِدُوا عَلَيْهِ جَازَتْ شَهَادَتُهُمْ\"."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.5178 - Musa ibn Bakr narrated from Zurarah from Abu Abdullah (as), who said:\n\"The practice of Qasamah (the collective oath) was established to impose severity upon a man known for evil and who is suspected. If they testify against him, their testimony is accepted.\""
        ]
      }
